The paper deals with data structures for efficiently answering range queries on a sequence, which is a classic problem in data structures. The use of compressed space and empirical entropy suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and data compression (cs.DM). The dynamic aspect of the data structure suggests a connection to dynamic data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of thresholds and majority/minority queries suggests a connection to machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.LG).
